    "summary": "Today, many companies see the urge to become Agile to attain a shorter time to market, better quality, higher productivity and an attractive work climate. Scrum teams are formed and product owners assigned. And yet the expected results are not being achieved.\n\nAs an agile consultant I help your company take steps to achieve your objectives. Clear priorities for all employees and a management style where trust is paramount are crucial in this respect. \n\nI have a coaching and facilitating leadership style, strong analytical skills and am always investigating new ways to create software that exceed the expectations of the client. I am a certified LeSS practitioner, SAFe agilist, Scrum master and Prince 2 project manager.  I prefer long term success above short term showcases. I proved to be pragmatic and successful even in not (yet) agile organisations. For me my assignment is a success when it brings the value intended by the stakeholders as well as a sustained improvement in co-operation and productivity.",
